cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with the placement and optimization of base stations for wireless communication networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also deals with resource allocation and optimization, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper proposes an algorithm to find efficient 3D locations of DBSs, which involves optimization and decision-making, and hence falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also considers the mobility of DBSs, which is related to control and system dynamics, and hence falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the effects of antenna beamwidth, which is related to multimedia and image processing, and hence falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
